defaultto lack of funding 
defaultand direction from central government.
default  Animal welfare is a low priority
default for
default Local Au
defaultthorities, 
defaultwhich, 
defaultwhilst regrettable
default,
default is understandable
default when resources are stretched thinly.
default 
defaultLegislation governing the private ownership or trade
default of animals
default, i.e. The Dangerous Wild Animals Act 1976, the Animal Welfare Act 2006 and the Pet Animals Act 1951
default are all broadly fit for purpose
default. Any
default failure of these Acts
default is due to problems with
default enforcement by Local Authorities that are 
defaultinadequate
